23/02/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The country is poised to host political leaders from the Balkans and international investors in what is described as the biggest conference BiH has ever held.
The presidents of Croatia, Serbia-Montenegro and Macedonia, as well as the prime ministers of Albania, Bulgaria, Croatia, and Slovenia will join businessmen from 53 countries in assessing about 300 projects.
The event will take place in Mostar from 26 February to 27 February.
In other news, a two-day international conference on fighting terrorism opens Monday in Sarajevo.
Officials from 15 countries will attend, including Russia and the United States.
(SRNA, BBC - 22/02/04;
AFP - 21/02/04)
